    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-dr-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA model ensemble meets pre-established acceptance criteria for all three QoIs across N=11 bench specimens tested at two independent laboratories. All E/uval values are below 1.96 and all percentage differences are below 10%. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The Test conditions factor achieves only Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3, which is accepted given the standardized and regulatory-mandated nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol. The overall credibility is judged sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision.",
